The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Easy for Indians on opening day
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Easy for Indians on opening day
                      
	Bangalore: Indian players, including Pankaj Advani, Rupesh Shah and Geet Sethi scored easy victories during the opening day of the IBSF World Billiards Championship here on Monday.         
	In league matches of the championship (points format), the trio scored easy 3-0 victories.         
	Defending champion (points format) Shah defeated SM Shaharwardi of Sri Lanka 151-53, 151-35, 150-21 while Advani beat Calum Hossack of Scotland 151-5, 150-0, 151-17. Sethi was too good for Teik Chong Alan Puan of Singapore 150-66, 151-93, 153-0.           (PTI)                                                                                                                      
